## üîë Story 1: Secure Access & Role-Based Control
**NOC Context:** "Before any automation runs, the system enforces strict security. Only authorized service accounts or operators can trigger actions."

### Step 1: Obtain Access Token
1.  Open **http://localhost:8000/docs**.
2.  Find **Authentication** -> `POST /api/v1/auth/token`.
3.  Click **Try it out**.
4.  Enter the following in the form:
    - **username:** `admin`
    - **password:** `admin` (Note: for the mock, password is the same as username)
5.  Click **Execute**.
6.  **Expected Result:** A JSON response with an [access_token](file:///Users/himanshu/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-himanshu@htadvisers.co.uk/My%20Drive/AI%20Learning/AntiGravity/Pedkai/backend/app/core/security.py#44-56). 
7.  **Action:** Copy the [access_token](file:///Users/himanshu/Library/CloudStorage/GoogleDrive-himanshu@htadvisers.co.uk/My%20Drive/AI%20Learning/AntiGravity/Pedkai/backend/app/core/security.py#44-56) string (without quotes). Click the **Authorize** lock icon at the top of the page, paste the token, and click **Authorize**.

